org.microbean.settings

Class Value

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microbean.settings.Value
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Supplier<String>

    public class Value
extends Object
implements Supplier<String>
    A Supplier of Strings and hence an abstraction of a (definitionally) String-typed setting value, additionally encompassing the setting name for which it is applicable and the Source whence it originated.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    Settings, Source, Source.getValue(String, Set)
    Thread Safety:
    Instances of this class are safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.

        public int hashCode()
        Returns a hashcode for this Value based off the return value of the get() method and nothing else.

        Note that because the return value of invocations of a Value's get() method can change over time, in general Value hashcodes should be treated with great care.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object other)
        Returns true if the supplied Object is a Value and has a get() method implementation that returns a value equal to the return value of an invocation of this Value's get() method.

        Note that because the return value of invocations of a Value's get() method can change over time, in general Value equality comparisons should be treated with great care.
